<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol type="1">
            <li>Open the Project Organizer or Content Explorer.</li>
            <li>Click the <span class="Emphasis">Show Files</span> button <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl/Interface/Buttons/Show-Files-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. The Project Organizer or Content Explorer splits into two halves (left and right).</li>
            <li>On the left side of the split Project Organizer or Content Explorer, select the folder containing the files to which you want to apply condition tags.</li>
            <li>On the right side of the split Project Organizer or Content Explorer, select the files. <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Hold-SHIFT-CTRL-Keys.flsnp" /></li>
            <li>In the toolbar click <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Ca-Co-Fl-Li/Interface/Buttons/Run-Properties-btn2.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. The Properties dialog opens.</li>
            <li>Click the <span class="Emphasis">Conditional Text</span> tab. The first condition tag set is selected and the associated condition tags are shown on the right.</li>
            <li>If you want to see condition tags for a different condition tag set, select it.</li>
            <li>For each condition tag that you want to apply to the files, click the check box next to the tag. A check mark appears in the box.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Click-OK.flsnp" /> The square next to the file name in the Project Organizer or Content Explorer now takes on the color of the condition tag. If you applied more than one condition tag to the file, each color is shown in the square. (If you do not see squares, click <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Ca-Co-Fl-Li-Mi/Interface/Buttons/Hide-Show-Conditional-Indicators-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> in the local toolbar.)</li>
            <li>To hide the split view, click the <span class="Emphasis">Show Files</span> button <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl/Interface/Buttons/Show-Files-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> again.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Save-File.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>